The paper discusses a new notion of algorithmic stability and privacy for releasing real-valued queries computed over a dataset. This topic is closely related to computer security (cs.CR) and machine learning (cs.LG), as well as data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), information theory (cs.IT), and social and information networks (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the composition guarantees of typical stability/privacy, which further supports the relevance to these sub-categories.
